@eyespy3001 Storytelling is fundamentally about the characters and their experiences. 

FX can definitely be an important part of the story (e.g. Star Wars), but if the CGI *is* the main character, there just won't be much to the story. (e.g. the Rings of Power--the characters are poorly written and the story is cactus. The star of the show is the CGI and the $ Bezos blew on it). 

You can have CGI characters, or even fully animated movies (or a stage play with no FX), but there needs to be a good story to tell. At this point we can CGI anything to look realistic, which is cool, but you don't end up with a good movie just because you have epic scenery and realistic explosions.

